  "issue_title": "[Bug] GraphQL PAT auth failures can restore stale cached PR rewards",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\nA stored miner PAT can pass REST `/user` validation but fail the PR GraphQL query used during scoring with an auth/scope error, for example:\n\n`Resource not accessible by personal access token`\n\n`load_miners_prs` marks `github_pr_fetch_failed=True`, but does not set `failed_reason`. Because cache fallback only skips miners with `failed_reason`, the validator can restore a previous successful cached evaluation and continue rewarding stale PRs even though the current PAT no longer has the GraphQL access scoring requires.\n\nThis is different from transient GitHub/network/resource-limit failures: an auth/scope failure is not self-healing until the miner submits a usable PAT.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Seed `MinerEvaluationCache` with a previous successful evaluation for a UID/hotkey/github_id.\n2. Run scoring for the same UID with a stored PAT that passes REST `/user`.\n3. Mock the PR GraphQL query to return:\n   `{\"errors\":[{\"message\":\"Resource not accessible by personal access token\"}],\"data\":null}`\n4. Call `store_or_use_cached_evaluation`.\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nGraphQL auth/scope failures should be treated as non-cacheable validation failures.\n\nThe miner should not receive stale cached rewards until they submit a PAT that can perform the GraphQL queries required for scoring.\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\n`failed_reason` remains `None`, `github_pr_fetch_failed=True`, `total_prs=0`, and cache fallback restores the old successful evaluation.\n\n## Environment\n\n- OS: Any validator environment\n- Python version: 3.12\n- Branch: current `test`\n\n## Additional Context\n\nRelated but not duplicate:\n\n- #515 / #516 fixed valid zero-PR results using stale cache.\n- #644 / #645 discussed transient per-PR fetch failures and was closed as not planned.\n- This issue is narrower: clear GraphQL PAT auth/scope failures should not be treated like transient GitHub outages.\n\nLikely fix: detect GraphQL auth/scope errors such as `Resource not accessible by personal access token`, set `failed_reason`, and preserve cache fallback for transient network/5xx/resource-limit failures.\n",
